#Text=Dapper Laughs
#Text=Dapper Laughs ( born 17 June 1984 in Kingston upon Thames , London , England ) is a pseudonym of Daniel O'Reilly .
#Text=He is a social media content creator from Addlestone , Surrey .
#Text=He has described himself as the " Moisturiser " . [ 1 ] [ 2 ]
#Text=Dapper Laughs became known on the social networking sites Facebook and Vine , where he has around 72,407,000 and 4,575,000 followers respectively .
#Text=Career and controversies
#Text=In 2014 , Laughs released the single " Proper Moist " . [ 3 ]

column1: #Text=The song entered the UK Singles Chart at number 15 .
#Text=Starting in 2014 , Laughs began his Moist Tour of the UK ; his supporting act on the tour was fellow Viner Joe Charman .
#Text=In July , he released " Take It To The Base " .
#Text=The music video was released on YouTube , but has since been made private .
#Text=In September 2014 , his show , entitled Dapper Laughs : On the Pull , began on ITV2 , where he tried to increase the participants ' chances of obtaining sex with women . [ 4 ] [ 5 ]
#Text=In November 2014 , Laughs criticised the website UsVsTh3m on Twitter for what he viewed as an unfavourable review of his new album Proper Naughty Christmas .
#Text=Laughs suggested that the review could hinder his goal of raising money for homelessness charity Shelter . [ 6 ]

#Text=As a result of UsVsTh3m highlighting the lyrics of one of the album tracks as offensive to the homeless , the charity posted on their official Twitter feed that they would be refusing donations from Laughs . [ 6 ]
#Text=Laughs later made an apology in a statement . [ 7 ]
#Text=Laughs was heavily criticised in November 2014 when , soon after accusations that his ITV show On The Pull was degrading to women , [ 8 ]
#Text=he joked that a female audience member at one of his live shows was " gagging for a rape . " [ 9 ]
#Text=An online petition eventually gained 68,210 signatures with the hashtag #CancelDapper asked ITV to end the series . [ 10 ]
#Text=On 10 November , ITV announced they were not renewing the series for a second season as a result . [ 11 ]
#Text=A forthcoming Dapper Laughs tour was also cancelled . [ 10 ]
#Text=On 11 November 2014 , Laughs announced on Newsnight that his Dapper Laughs character had been indefinitely retired .
#Text=When interviewed on the BBC programme , he claimed he did not realise the problems he had caused .
#Text=Laughs also claimed that the media played a major role in the anger directed at him . [ 12 ]
#Text=In December that year , Laughs resurrected the character . [ 13 ]
#Text=On 25 December 2014 , a YouTube and Facebook video was posted stating that Laughs ' character Dapper Laughs would be making a return with the promise of toned down content .
#Text=On 15 January 2015 , he announced his " The Res'Erection " stand-up show . [ 14 ]

column1: #Text=On 8 March 2015 a pilot for a web-exclusive sitcom based on the character was uploaded to YouTube .
#Text=On 22 January 2017 , Laughs took part in a charity amateur boxing match at Aldershot Princes Hall , where he defeated his opponent marginally , 10/9/10 being the judges score .
#Text=This was held in support of Help for Heroes .
#Text=In an interview , Laughs described how he would be happy to face fellow comedian Jack Jones , also of social media fame , and that he would " have him " .
#Text=In January 2018 , Laughs entered the Celebrity Big Brother house as a housemate during its twenty-first series . [ 15 ]
#Text=He was the eighth housemate to be evicted .
#Text=Personal life
#Text=Daniel has two daughters , named Neve O’Reilly and Roux O’Reilly . [ 16 ] [ 17 ]
#Text=He proposed to his longtime girlfriend Shelly Broadhurst in January 2018 , during his eviction interview on Celebrity Big Brother . [ 18 ]
